Enable Debug Mode in Eclipse (Run Configurations)
----------------------------------------------------
1. Right-click on the test class → Run As → Run Configurations
2. Go to the "Environment" tab
3. Click "Add" →

Variable: PWDEBUG
Value: 1
Click Apply → Run
This will start Playwright in debug mode inside Eclipse.

Run a test from a specific breakpoint
----------------------------------------
Insert the following line at the desired point in your test:
page.pause();

Run your tests in debug mode. 
Clicking the "Resume" button in the Inspector will run the test and only stop on the page.pause().